1
00:00:00,027 --> 00:00:04,609
The church was built in partnership with a Syriac Orthodox family

2
00:00:04,634 --> 00:00:06,276
That family was the Sarsab family

3
00:00:06,301 --> 00:00:13,125
And the Chakmakjian family, known for its charitable works

4
00:00:13,150 --> 00:00:15,052
And for providing many donations

5
00:00:15,077 --> 00:00:16,796
Not only to the Armenians

6
00:00:16,821 --> 00:00:18,568
But to the whole city of Mosul

7
00:00:18,593 --> 00:00:20,964
It was a very well known family

8
00:00:20,989 --> 00:00:23,880
Along with other families

9
00:00:23,905 --> 00:00:29,115
That contributed much support

10
00:00:29,140 --> 00:00:31,796
And left their mark

11
00:00:31,821 --> 00:00:34,739
Such as Grigor Astarjian

12
00:00:34,922 --> 00:00:39,453
This well known doctor, whose palace stood beside the Prophet Younes Mosque

13
00:00:39,818 --> 00:00:43,099
It was one of the palaces that hosted many figures

14
00:00:43,124 --> 00:00:48,049
Both Arab and international, when they visited Mosul, due to the lack of hotels

15
00:00:48,074 --> 00:00:53,154
In addition, there were Armenians who contributed

16
00:00:53,179 --> 00:00:59,247
In the field of sports, where there was the Armenian Homenetmen Club

17
00:00:59,272 --> 00:01:05,341
Many of its athletes became prominent in the Mosul sports scene
